COMMENT : The invasive moderately differentiated mucinous adenocarcinoma shows a variety of architectural patterns with lepidic and papillary patterns predominant .
although the areas of invasion show the predominance of acinar growth .

PAS , PAS-D and mucicarmine stains are strongly positive in the neoplastic cells .
WG stains show visceral pleural invasion ( D Block ) .
lmmunoperoxidase stains show that the tumor cells are negative for p63 and oytokeratin 516 and fail to express TTF-1 .
Grocott and-acid-fast stains are negative .
sections of the part1 " right sixth rib " show normal bone and bone marrow with trilineage representation and maturation .
No evidence of maiignancy is seen .

BACKGROUND : EGFR mutations are present in about 10-1 5 % of non-Asian and up to 40 % of the Asian patients with non-small-cell lung cancer ( NSCLC ) ( 1.2 ) .
They are more frequent in non-smokersrfemales , and in tumors with adenocarcinoma histology .
Activating EGFR mutations including exon 19 deletions , exon 21 point mutations ( L858R .
and exon 18 G719AlClS point mutation are associated with the clinical response to treatment with EGFR tyrosine kinase inhibitors ( TKI ) ( ge?tinib , erlotinib ) ( 2-4 ) .
Advanced NSCLC patients with activating EGFR mutations show response rates of more than 70 % , with progression-free survival up to 14 month ( 2.3 ) .
However .
EGFR mutations inexon 20 ( insertions and T790iili point mutation ) are associated with acquired resistance to TKis ( 4 ) .
KRAS mutations and BRAF mutations are found In approximately 30 % and 2 % of lung adenocarcinomas respectively .
The most common mutation types are KRAS codon ? i2l13 and BRAF VBOOE .
Patients with these mutations tend to be resistant to eriotinib and ge?tinib ( 25.6 ) .
However , not all tumors reveal such a correlation and , therefore , the results of molecular testing should be interpreted in conjunction with other laboratory and clinical ?ndings .
